<DOCUMENT source-infobase-name="Rules" content-collection-id="NYCrules" source-infobase-title="The Rules of the City of New York" base-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\" default-split-level="Chapter" makefile-filename="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\NYCrules.mak" css-stylesheet-href="#!-- #ID=NYCrules_css_id --#" xml-output-dir="D:\process\NFOProcess\codes\ny\newyorkcity\NYCrules\output\HUCCVLERTKEUARDR\XML\" css-stylesheet-name="NYCrules_css" makefile-document-depth="2">
	<LEVEL style-name="Chapter" style-name-escaped="Chapter" style-id="0-0-0-477" level-depth="2" toc-section="false">
		<RECORD id="0-0-0-105407" number="51036" version="814">
			<HEADING>Chapter 5: Pet Shops</HEADING>
			<PARA>
				<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-14860" name="T24C005"/>Chapter 5: Pet Shops</PARA>
		</RECORD>
		<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
			<RECORD id="0-0-0-105412" number="51037" version="3025">
				<PARA style-name="EdNoteSm" style-name-escaped="EdNoteSm" style-id="0-0-0-20">
					<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Editor&apos;s note:</CHARFORMAT> This chapter, originally based on material published in City Record 3/6/2018, eff. 4/5/2018, was repealed and reenacted in CIty Record 2/17/2026, eff. 3/19/2026) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
				</PARA>
			</RECORD>
		</LEVEL>
		<LEVEL style-name="Subchapter" style-name-escaped="Subchapter" style-id="0-0-0-480" level-depth="3" toc-section="false">
			<LEVEL style-name="Subtitle" style-name-escaped="Subtitle" style-id="0-0-0-15301" level-depth="4" toc-section="false">
				<LEVEL style-name="Part" style-name-escaped="Part" style-id="0-0-0-483" level-depth="5" toc-section="false">
					<LEVEL style-name="Subpart" style-name-escaped="Subpart" style-id="0-0-0-15960" level-depth="6" toc-section="false">
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-155087" number="51038" version="3025">
								<HEADING>§ 5-01 Scope and Applicability.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-14862" name="T24C005_5-01"/>§ 5-01 Scope and Applicability.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-105420" number="51039" version="3025">
									<PARA>This Chapter contains rules applicable to pet shops as defined in New York City Administrative Code § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="17-371" destination-id="0-0-0-0">17-371</LINK> or successor provision. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-105446" number="51040" version="3025">
									<PARA>(Added CIty Record 2/17/2026, eff. 3/19/2026) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-105419" number="51041" version="814">
								<HEADING>§ 5-02 Definitions.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-14864" name="T24C005_5-02"/>§ 5-02 Definitions.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-105443" number="51042" version="3025">
									<PARA>When used in this Chapter, the following terms have the following meanings: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155086" number="51043" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>“<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Animal rescue group</CHARFORMAT>” has the same meaning as in § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="17-802" destination-id="0-0-0-0">17-802</LINK> of the Administrative Code. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155085" number="51044" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>“<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Animal shelter</CHARFORMAT>” has the same meaning as in § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="17-802" destination-id="0-0-0-0">17-802</LINK> of the Administrative Code. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155084" number="51045" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>“<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Cat</CHARFORMAT>” has the same meaning as in 24 RCNY Health Code § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T24HC_161.02" destination-id="0-0-0-6983">161.02</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155083" number="51046" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>“<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Dog</CHARFORMAT>” has the same meaning as in 24 RCNY Health Code § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T24HC_161.02" destination-id="0-0-0-6983">161.02</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155082" number="51047" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>“<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Health Code</CHARFORMAT>” means the New York City Health Code. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155081" number="51048" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>“<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Pet shop</CHARFORMAT>” has the same meaning as in § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="671734137-329684122-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Admin.nfo" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="17-371" destination-id="0-0-0-0">17-371</LINK> of the Administrative Code. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155080" number="51049" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>“<CHARFORMAT bold="1" italic="0" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Small animal</CHARFORMAT>” has the same meaning as in 24 RCNY Health Code § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T24HC_161.02" destination-id="0-0-0-6983">161.02</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-105442" number="51050" version="3025">
									<PARA>(Added CIty Record 2/17/2026, eff. 3/19/2026) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-105418" number="51051" version="3025">
								<HEADING>§ 5-03 Prohibition.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-14866" name="T24C005_5-03"/>§ 5-03 Prohibition.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-105429" number="51052" version="3025">
									<PARA>No pet shop may display, sell, lease, offer to lease, offer to sell, barter, auction, give away or otherwise transfer ownership of any dog, cat, guinea pig or rabbit. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-105417" number="51053" version="3025">
									<PARA>(Added CIty Record 2/17/2026, eff. 3/19/2026) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-155088" number="51054" version="3025">
								<HEADING>§ 5-04 Disposition of and Restrictions on Permits.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-14868" name="T24C005_5-04"/>§ 5-04 Disposition of and Restrictions on Permits.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-105423" number="51055" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Permit authorizing sale of dogs or cats.</CHARFORMAT> Any permit issued by the Department authorizing the permittee to sell or offer for sale of dogs or cats lapsed by operation of law effective December 15, 2024 and is null and void. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155092" number="51056" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Permit authorizing the sale of small animals other than dogs and cats.</CHARFORMAT> The holder of a permit issued pursuant to 24 RCNY Health Code § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T24HC_161.09" destination-id="0-0-0-6997">161.09</LINK> must not sell or offer for sale animals other than small animals authorized by such permit and for which possession is not prohibited by 24 RCNY Health Code § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T24HC_161.00" destination-id="0-0-0-15035">161.01</LINK> and transfer is not prohibited by 24 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T24C005_5-03" destination-id="0-0-0-14866">5-03</LINK>. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-105416" number="51057" version="3025">
									<PARA>(Added CIty Record 2/17/2026, eff. 3/19/2026) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-155089" number="51058" version="3025">
								<HEADING>§ 5-05 Adoption Promotions with Certain Non-Profits.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-14870" name="T24C005_5-05"/>§ 5-05 Adoption Promotions with Certain Non-Profits.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-105426" number="51059" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>A person or entity operating an establishment selling or offering for sale small animals other than dogs, cats, rabbits, and guinea pigs, may allow an animal shelter or non-profit animal rescue group to use its facilities to offer animals for adoption provided that it satisfies the following requirements: <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155095" number="51060" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Must obtain a copy of either a valid permit issued to the animal shelter by the Commissioner pursuant to 24 RCNY Health Code § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T24HC_161.09" destination-id="0-0-0-6997">161.09</LINK>, or proof of the animal rescue group’s incorporated not-for-profit status. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155094" number="51061" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Whenever the animal shelter or animal rescue group is offering animals for adoption at the establishment, the establishment must have on site, and available for inspection upon request, a copy of the animal shelter’s permit or animal rescue group’s registration with the New York State Department of Agriculture and Markets Registered Rescues and Shelters List, and the animal shelter’s or animal rescue group’s proof of not-for-profit status, and the animal shelter or animal rescue group’s registration of such status and exemption from the definition of ‘pet dealer’, issued by the New York State Department of Agriculture and Markets pursuant to section 408 of the New York State Agriculture and Markets Law. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155093" number="51062" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>A pet shop is not required to comply with the requirements of 24 RCNY §§ <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T24C005_5-03" destination-id="0-0-0-14866">5-03</LINK> and <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T24C005_5-04" destination-id="0-0-0-14868">5-04</LINK> regarding any dog or cat offered for adoption by an animal shelter or animal rescue group using such pet shop’s facilities, provided that such pet shop does not have an ownership interest in such animal. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-105415" number="51063" version="3025">
									<PARA>(Added CIty Record 2/17/2026, eff. 3/19/2026) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-155090" number="51064" version="3025">
								<HEADING>§ 5-06 Enforcement.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-14872" name="T24C005_5-06"/>§ 5-06 Enforcement.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-105425" number="51065" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Summons and penalty.</CHARFORMAT>&#160;<HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155102" number="51066" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(1)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Any person or entity found to be displaying, offering for sale, leasing, delivering, bartering, auctioning, giving away or transferring a dog, cat, rabbit or guinea pig in violation of 24 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T24C005_5-03" destination-id="0-0-0-14866">5-03</LINK> will be issued a summons subject to a penalty of $500 per day and per animal. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155103" number="51067" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(2)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Any person or entity found to be in violation of 24 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T24C005_5-04" destination-id="0-0-0-14868">5-04</LINK>(b) shall be issued a summons subject to a penalty of $500. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155100" number="51068" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Seizure.</CHARFORMAT> The Department may seize any dog, cat, rabbit or guinea pig found on premises operated as a pet shop or other entity that is prohibited from selling, leasing, offering to sell or lease, barter, auction or otherwise transfer these animals. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155099" number="51069" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Forfeiture.</CHARFORMAT> Any dog, cat, rabbit or guinea pig seized pursuant to this section is subject to forfeiture after notice and hearing unless the Department, in its sole discretion, allows the owner to reclaim the animal. If the Department allows the owner to reclaim the animal, it may impose any terms and conditions to reclamation it deems appropriate. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155098" number="51070" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(d)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Impoundment and disposition.</CHARFORMAT> The Department may provide for the appropriate disposition of any dog, cat, rabbit or guinea pig seized pursuant to this section. Such disposition may include impoundment at an animal shelter or by an animal rescue group. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155097" number="51071" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(e)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Expenses.</CHARFORMAT> The Department may impose upon the owner of any animal seized pursuant to this section a fee for the Department’s expenses incurred in connection with seizing or impounding such animal. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-155096" number="51072" version="3025">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(f)<TAB tab-count="1"/>
										<CHARFORMAT bold="0" italic="1" underline="0" strike-out="0" hidden="0">Authorized agents.</CHARFORMAT> Employees or designees of the Department and officers of the NYPD are authorized to enforce the provisions of this Chapter. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-119]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-105414" number="51073" version="3025">
